# No barrel `index.ts` files

- **Do not create** `index.ts` (or `index.tsx`) files whose **only purpose** is to import symbols from other files in the same folder and re-export them (“barrel file”).
- **Import directly** from the defining module instead (e.g. `@/features/foo/components/widget` rather than `@/features/foo`).

## Why

Barrel files add indirection, slow tooling resolution, and encourage unclear dependency graphs without real benefit in this repo.

## Allowed

- **`index.ts` is fine** when it contains real logic (not only re-exports), e.g. a route handler or a module that wires several pieces together with implementation.
- **Framework conventions** (e.g. Next.js `app/**/page.tsx`, package entry points required by tooling) take precedence when they are not “barrel-only” patterns.

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — barrel-only
// features/chat/tools/index.ts
export { chatTools } from "./chat-tools";
export { generateImageTool } from "./generate-image.tool";

// ✅ GOOD — consumers import from the concrete file
import { chatTools } from "@/features/chat/tools/chat-tools";
```
